text:
18 pm Fire crews respond to large industrial blaze east of Edmonton By Phil Heidenreich Online journalist Global News 
Strathcona County Fire Services were called to a structure fire on 17 Street between 90 Avenue and 92 Avenue on Feb. 6, 2017. Les Knight/ Global News   Listen 
The RCMP said officers and Strathcona County Fire Services firefighters were called to a structure fire on 17 Street between 90 Avenue and 92 Avenue on Monday evening. 
Police said the fire was burning in an industrial area and the public was being asked to stay away from the fire, which is about halfway between Edmonton and Sherwood Park. 
According to the RCMP, no fatalities or injuries were reported and they were unaware of an air quality advisories. They did not say what was in the building that caught fire.
